Privacy Policy for Yotell

Last updated: [Date]

Welcome to Yotell, a social media platform designed to connect people around shared interests and activities. Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how Yotell collects, uses, and protects your personal information when you use our services.

Information We Collect:

Personal Information: When you sign up for Yotell, we collect your name, email address, and profile information you choose to provide (e.g., bio, profile picture).
Usage Information: We gather information about how you use Yotell, such as your interactions with posts, messages, and other users.
Device Information: We may collect device information such as your IP address, browser type, and device identifiers.
How We Use Your Information:

Providing Services: We use your information to operate, maintain, and improve Yotell, including personalizing your experience and suggesting content.
Communication: We may send you notifications and updates related to your account or our services.
Analytics: We analyze usage trends to understand how users interact with Yotell and to improve our services.
Sharing Your Information:

With Your Consent: We may share your information with third parties when you give us consent to do so.
Service Providers: We work with service providers who help us with hosting, analytics, customer support, and other functions necessary to operate Yotell.
Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information if required by law or to protect our rights or the rights of others.
Data Security:

We implement security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction.
Your Choices:

You can manage your account settings and update your information through Yotell.
You can opt-out of receiving certain communications from us.
